E. O. TARVER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11335. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 28, 1946. Cannon & Callister, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Charles H. Carr, U. S. Atty., and James M. Carter, Ernest A. Tolin, and Arthur Livingston, Asst. U. S. Atty., all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, BONE, and ORR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
